Proto-Proposal
---
Auctions

 Enact a Rule, titled "Auctions", reading :

   Whenever the Rules call for an Auction to be held, the Player
   responsible for holding the Auction, or Auctioneer, shall announce
   that fact to the Public Forum as soon as possible, together with the
   identity of the Seller. For a period of one Week after such an
   announcement is posted, all Players, with the exception of any
   Players made ineligible by other Rules, may post Bids to the Public
   Forum.

   As soon as possible after the Auction ends, the Auctioneer shall
   announce the identity of the Winner of the Auction, if any, and any
   effects of the Auction specified in the Rules shall take place at the
   time of this announcement.

 Enact a Rule, titled "Bidding", reading :

   Bidding in an Auction consists of a naming an amount or amounts of 
   any number of Currencies which are specifically determined by the 
   Rules or which are designated as Traded Currencies.

   At the end of the Auction's bidding period, the Auctioneer shall 
   rank all valid Bids received. Bids are ranked by determining the 
   total, expressed in the Reference Currency, of all amounts of 
   Currencies named therein, at the Exchange Rate which was current 
   when the Auction started.

   The Bidder who submitted the highest ranking Bid is entitled to 
   become the Winner of the Auction, and to do so must transfer all 
   Currencies named in that Bid to the Seller within three days. If 
   that Bidder fails to do so within three days, or before that time 
   informs the Auctioneer that e is withdrawing from the Auction, the 
   Bidder who submitted the next highest ranking Bid shall be so 
   entitled, with the same strictures. The Auction ends whenever a 
   Bidder has exercised eir right to become Winner, or all Bidders 
   have withdrawn or failed to exercise that right.

   If the Auction being held is designated by the Rules as an Open
   Auction, Bids, retractions and payments shall only be valid if sent
   to the Public Forum.

 Enact a Rule, titled "Auctioning Currencies", reading :

   Any Player is authorized, once in any Week, to call for an Auction 
   to sell some of eir property. The announcement of the Auction 
   shall list amounts of any number Currencies, known as the 
   Auctioned Property.

   That Player shall be the Auctioneer and Seller. The Winner of the
   Auction shall be authorized to submit Payment Orders naming emself
   as Payee and the Seller as Payor, for all amounts of Currencies 
   named as the Auctioned Property.

[For the moment, this is dependent on the Currency Market proto for
a total ordering of Bids; if that fails to be finalized promptly, I
will go back to the partial ordering I suggested previously, as well
as the more complex Bidding rules this involves.]

